{"abstract":[{"text":"Joystick view used to control various activities such as moving a character on the screen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The View creates a Rectangular region to act as a hitbox for drag gestures. Once a drag","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is initiated the joystick appears on screen centered at the start location of the gesture. While","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dragging, the thumb of the joystick is limited be within the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"radius"},{"text":" of the sticks background circle.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders"]]},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:7Sliders8JoystickV","modules":[{"name":"Sliders"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","title":"Joystick","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Joystick","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Joystick","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"2D-Controls","title":"2D Controls","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/TrackPad","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/RadialPad"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Joystick","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"state","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding<JoyState>"},{"text":"  you provide a binding to a Joystate  value which allows you to maintain access to all of the Joysticks state values","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Double"},{"text":" The radius of the track","type":"text"}]}],"name":"radius"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A boolean value describing whether the joystick has locking behavior (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default: true","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}],"name":"canLock"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bool"},{"type":"text","text":" whether the joystick allows hit testing or not ("},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default: false","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}],"name":"isDisabled"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Style","anchor":"Style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Joystick can be themed and styled by making a custom struct conforming to the "},{"code":"JoystickStyle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"protocol. Conformance requires that you implement 4 methods"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"1.  "},{"code":"makeHitBox","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the rectangular region that responds the the users touch"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"code":"makeLockBox","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates a view such that if the drag gestures location is contained within the lockbox, the joystick goes into the locked state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"3.  "},{"code":"makeTrack","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the circular track that contains the joystick thumb"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"4   "},{"code":"makeThumb","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - Creates the part of the joystick the moves when dragging"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"These 3 methods all provide access to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"JoystickConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" ."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Make use of the various state values to customize the Joystick to your liking."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["    struct JoystickConfiguration {","        let isDisabled: Bool \/\/ whether or not the slider is current disables","        let isActive: Bool \/\/ True if the joystick thumb is dragging or if the joystick is locked","        let isAtLimit: Bool \/\/ whether the offset of the thumb reached the radius of the circle","        let isLocked: Bool \/\/ Whether the joystick is locked or not","        let angle: Angle \/\/ The angle of the line between the pads center and the thumbs location, measured from the vector pointing in the trailing direction","        let radialOffset: Double \/\/ The current displacement of the thumb from the track's center","     }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once your custom style has been created, implement it by calling the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"joystickStyle(_ :)"},{"type":"text","text":" method on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Joystick"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a view containing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Joystick"},{"type":"text","text":" to be styled. To make it easier try using the follow example based upon the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultJoystickStyle"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["     struct <#My Joystick Style#>: JoystickStyle {","         func makeHitBox(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Rectangle()","                 .fill(Color.white.opacity(0.05))","         }","         func makeLockBox(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.black)","                 .overlay(Circle().fill(Color.yellow).scaleEffect(0.7))","                 .frame(width: 25, height: 25)","         }","         func makeTrack(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.gray.opacity(0.4))","         }","         func makeThumb(configuration: JoystickConfiguration) -> some View {","             Circle()","                 .fill(Color.blue)","                 .frame(width: 45, height: 45)","","         }","     }"]}]}],"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/Sliders\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/Sliders\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/init(state:radius:)","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/init(state:radius:canLock:isDisabled:)","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/init(state:radius:isDisabled:)"],"generated":true},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/body","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/state"],"generated":true},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/sliders\/joystick"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/Joystick"},"references":{"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders/Joystick/state":{"title":"state","kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/sliders\/joystick\/state","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"state","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": 